<FIRST>r i AM--BRF-WhiteTigers     06-25 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM--BRF-White Tigers,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rare White Tigers Debut At Swedish Zoo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Amur and Flurry, two white tigers
obtained from a Chicago zoo, have made their first public appearance
in Sweden.
   Large crowds turned out at Eskilstuna Zoo on Saturday to view
Amur, 6, and Flurry, 3, who had been in quarantine since arriving
from Chicago in February.
   The tigers have mated at the zoo and hopes are high that Flurry
is pregnant, Lasse Karlsson, head of the Eskilstuna Zoo, told the TT
news agency.
   The white tiger, which has black stripes, is nearly extinct, and
zoos around the world have started a breeding project to try to save
them.
   Amur and Flurry, the only white tigers in a European zoo, are
descended from a white male tiger captured in 1951, TT said.
</TEXT>
