his informal practice of not taking questions during photo-taking
sessions.
   The president teamed up with House Minority Leader Robert Michel,
R-Ill., while Hawke was paired with Secretary of State James A.
Baker III.
   Michel is known as one of the best golfers in Congress and when
Bush tossed three golf balls to decide the pairings and won Michel
as a teammate, Baker quipped, ``The fix is on.''
   ``The fix is on already,'' agreed Hawke.
   Notwithstanding Bush's initial effort to minimize his game, the
president outdrove the other members of the foursome on the first
two holes. The two pairs were tied after two holes when reporters
were escorted off the course.
   The foursome finished the 18 holes in about three and one-half
hours. The president, asked about the outcome, said only, ``very
close, very close.''
   Hawke presented his hosts with gift putters and golf shirts.
