fatally shot. Police did not give the motive but blamed the killing
on Shining Path rebels.
   On Sunday an army colonel was wounded by gunmen as he left his
home in Lima.
   The Shining Path movement emerged in May 1980 and since then the
government says more than 14,000 people have been killed in violence
related to the insurgency.
